WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:02.469
- but it's not quite done yet.
- I need to see it.

00:02.536 --> 00:04.905
I was going to put
on the finishing touches
and show you later.

00:04.972 --> 00:06.840
This is the finishing TOUCH:
My seeing what you've done

00:06.907 --> 00:09.109
- With my dance and then
swearing a lot.
- Okay fine.

00:09.176 --> 00:10.978
But you need to keep
an open mind.

00:11.044 --> 00:12.713
- I always have
an open mind.
- right.

00:12.779 --> 00:15.048
But you need to keep
an open mind like other people
keep an open mind.

00:15.115 --> 00:17.117
With a mind that's
actually, you know, open.

00:17.184 --> 00:19.186
How many times
have I told you
my production

00:19.253 --> 00:22.055
- of "the nutcracker" is
the highlight of my year?
- 842.

00:22.122 --> 00:25.058
And how many times
have I told you that
these two weeks of shows

00:25.125 --> 00:28.262
- Make up the bulk
of my money for the year?
- 12,064.

00:28.328 --> 00:31.231
- I gave you
one dance to choreograph.
- The evil rat dance, yes.

00:31.298 --> 00:32.065
- mice!
- What?

00:32.132 --> 00:34.034
- Mice, they're evil mice.
- No difference.

00:34.101 --> 00:37.137
- Big difference.
- Whatever. Anyhow,
it's done

00:37.204 --> 00:40.274
and it's great.
I just put my own
spin on it is all.

00:40.340 --> 00:42.910
Are they wearing pasties
and g-Strings?

00:42.976 --> 00:45.379
Ahh, see, funny--
Like I made them
vegas stripper rats.

00:45.445 --> 00:46.880
- Mice.
- whatever.

00:46.947 --> 00:48.248
No, I just
moderned it up a bit.

00:48.315 --> 00:50.017
Plus I needed someone
to stand in for Clara,

00:50.083 --> 00:52.519
since we still don't have
a Clara, so there's
a temp in there.

00:52.586 --> 00:56.223
Terrific. You can
dictate your resignation
letter to her afterwards.

01:06.834 --> 01:08.802
♪ Sa-Sha! ♪

01:15.008 --> 01:17.177
Okay, make mama look good.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.418
<i>( music playing )</i>

02:27.114 --> 02:29.650
You get it?

02:29.716 --> 02:33.120
The rats are like
wall street guys 'cause
wall street guys are... rats?

02:33.187 --> 02:35.422
- I get it.
- Do you like it?

02:39.393 --> 02:42.296
- I love it.
- ( sighs of relief )

02:46.500 --> 02:48.101
- and they're mice.
- Whatever.

02:52.706 --> 02:54.107
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

03:13.961 --> 03:15.229
Opening weekend's
sold out.

03:15.295 --> 03:16.063
Nice.
Hot mustard.

03:16.129 --> 03:18.932
Mid-Week looks
a little slow.

03:18.999 --> 03:20.033
It'll pick up.
Moo Shu pork.

03:20.100 --> 03:23.337
Everything's down this year.

03:23.403 --> 03:27.307
Ticket sales, enrollments...
hopefully that fundraiser
you're organizing

03:27.374 --> 03:29.510
- Will make up the difference.
- Fundraiser?

03:29.576 --> 03:31.845
Yes, the fundraiser.

03:31.912 --> 03:34.314
The fundraiser
at the oyster bar.

03:34.381 --> 03:38.218
The one that
you said you'd plan,
that you had completely handled.

03:38.285 --> 03:39.052
- the one that--
- ( chuckles )

03:39.119 --> 03:42.055
- I hate you.
- <i>Everything's set--</i>

03:42.122 --> 03:44.057
Menu, decorations,
sound system.

03:44.124 --> 03:45.959
I got a weekend
at Catalina to raffle off,

03:46.026 --> 03:48.061
and I even got Rico
to donate the place for free.

03:48.128 --> 03:51.365
Speechless!

03:51.431 --> 03:53.967
- You're pretty proud
of yourself, aren't you?
- Yep.

03:54.034 --> 03:56.904
What would you say

03:56.970 --> 03:59.006
to running this place alone?

03:59.072 --> 04:00.040
For a while, anyway.

04:00.107 --> 04:03.644
Michael brought up Montana
again last night.

04:03.710 --> 04:06.346
He's talked about it
on and off for years.
I don't think he's ever

04:06.413 --> 04:09.550
been there for more than
a few days, But he has this
romantic notion about it.

04:09.616 --> 04:11.018
Anyhow, I was thinking

04:11.084 --> 04:13.754
since things are going
very smoothly around here...

04:13.820 --> 04:16.089
- since I've been around.
- ...I thought maybe
Michael and I

04:16.156 --> 04:19.193
could get away for a while.
I found this wonderful cabin--

04:19.259 --> 04:21.128
<i>Very rustic,</i>
<i>But completely comfortable.</i>

04:21.195 --> 04:24.231
I thought I could surprise him
and rent it for a couple,
three months.

04:24.298 --> 04:26.300
So romantic.
I'd be happy

04:26.366 --> 04:28.035
to take over while you
hang in the mountains
with your boyfriend.

04:28.101 --> 04:32.306
- Thank you.
- Which one of you is
going to be Heath ledger?

04:32.372 --> 04:35.542
You always
end the conversation
one sentence too late.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.044
- I'm here!
- <i>( bag drops )</i>

04:37.110 --> 04:39.546
- ( whispers ) Oh no!
- What?

04:39.613 --> 04:42.649
Oh crap!
I forgot all about her.

04:42.716 --> 04:44.852
- Who, the kid?
- That's no kid.

04:44.918 --> 04:47.688
- I'm ready!
- Okay, good!

04:47.754 --> 04:48.121
Ready for what?

04:53.026 --> 04:55.696
Whoa-- Holy crap.
Who is she?

04:55.762 --> 04:57.598
- The Ringer.
- What?

04:57.664 --> 05:00.601
When Sasha quit
and I couldn't find
anyone else I got desperate

05:00.667 --> 05:03.537
and I called the Ringer.
I had her shipped down
from San Francisco.

05:03.604 --> 05:05.539
- <i>What's her name?</i>
- <i>I don't know her name.</i>

05:05.606 --> 05:08.175
<i>She's always</i>
<i>just been called the Ringer.</i>
<i>What am I going to do?</i>

05:08.242 --> 05:10.844
- Fanny, you have to tell her
Sasha's back.
- I know I do.

05:12.112 --> 05:14.982
- Jiminy cricket!
- She's terrifying.

05:15.048 --> 05:17.217
If Marvel comics had
a crime-Fighting ballerina,

05:17.284 --> 05:19.186
this ballerina would kick
that ballerina's ass.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.589
You're talking.

05:22.656 --> 05:25.092
- No, no one's--
- She's talking.
I'm watching.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.127
I'm not talking.
I'm not talking!

05:27.194 --> 05:29.329
why don't you take
a break for a second?

05:40.541 --> 05:42.543
Good luck, cowboy.

05:42.609 --> 05:44.978
Wait!

05:45.045 --> 05:47.080
Break's over.

06:00.761 --> 06:04.631
- What is that?
- Sophia: I don't know,
but I'm learning to type.

06:04.698 --> 06:08.001
You don't think
madame Fanny actually...

06:14.741 --> 06:17.511
great.
Very mature.

06:17.578 --> 06:20.314
Hey, what is the what?
I'm starving.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.884
- Where do you guys
stash the Candy bars?
- Dancers don't eat Candy bars.

06:23.951 --> 06:26.019
Yeah right.
Suzanne Farrell
was 60% caramel.

06:26.086 --> 06:28.589
Can we help you
with something?

06:28.655 --> 06:30.023
I just came up to check
the state of the room,

06:30.090 --> 06:33.093
make sure
it's still pink.
It is.

06:36.830 --> 06:40.300
- What's going on here?
- Apparently while I was off
making with the pom-Poms

06:40.367 --> 06:43.504
some sort of blood feud
happened and no one seems
ready to let it go

06:43.570 --> 06:45.772
( loudly )
No matter how Boring
it's getting!

06:45.839 --> 06:48.542
Huh.
Anything I can help with?

06:50.410 --> 06:52.446
Okay, you four,
front and center.

06:52.513 --> 06:53.046
Why me?
I'm not in a fight.

06:53.113 --> 06:56.617
You need a fourth.
Watch "the craft." Move.

07:00.287 --> 07:02.189
Okay, as the NEW
sort-of-Promoted-

07:02.256 --> 07:04.057
Kind-of-Equal-
Not-Quite-a-partner-But-
Definitely-Someone-

07:04.124 --> 07:08.128
With-More-Authority-
Than-She-Had-Yesterday,
I am ordering you to spill.

07:12.566 --> 07:15.269
Boo likes Charlie,
Charlie likes Ginny,

07:15.335 --> 07:18.038
Melanie says Ginny can't
date Charlie because boo
liked him first,

07:18.105 --> 07:20.040
but Ginny thinks
since Boo likes Carl
she relinquishes Charlie,

07:20.107 --> 07:24.545
who should revert back
to the open market. And me,
I wish we were all lesbians.

07:24.611 --> 07:27.247
Wow, okay, uh... Ginny,
you like Charlie.

07:27.314 --> 07:30.217
- and he likes me.
- And, Melanie, you think
she shouldn't date him?

07:30.284 --> 07:32.653
- Boo has dibs.
- So you like him for boo?

07:32.719 --> 07:35.756
- I don't like him for anyone.
- But if boo wants Carl

07:35.822 --> 07:38.358
and is okay with Ginny
dating Charlie,

07:38.425 --> 07:41.195
could you find a way
to possibly to be okay
with it at all?

07:41.261 --> 07:44.131
The alterative being you might
lose a really perky friend.

07:44.198 --> 07:46.433
- I'll deal.
- Really?

07:46.500 --> 07:49.903
On the condition that I never
have to hear anything
about Charlie-- Ever.

07:49.970 --> 07:52.906
Nothing about his hair
or his car or his creepy
chicken hands.

07:52.973 --> 07:55.309
I promise.
I won't talk to you
about Charlie at all.

07:55.375 --> 07:57.044
- fine.
- Boo?

07:57.110 --> 08:00.047
- Charlie doesn't like me.
- not the point.

08:00.113 --> 08:03.116
- the point is that...
- I like Carl.

08:03.183 --> 08:06.119
- Yes. So...?
- It's fine.

08:06.186 --> 08:08.021
- You dating Charlie is fine.
- Good give.

08:08.088 --> 08:11.425
Now what are you gonna
do for her, blondie?

08:11.491 --> 08:13.060
- No more short-Carl jokes--
From either of us.
- What?!

08:13.126 --> 08:16.029
we will be completely nice
to him and we'll help you
get him back.

08:16.096 --> 08:19.433
C'mon!
I haven't called him
bilbo baggins yet!

08:19.499 --> 08:20.968
- Michelle: <i>Melanie!</i>
- Fine.

08:21.034 --> 08:23.770
Well handled.
Okay, uh, gum wrapper.

08:23.837 --> 08:27.007
Okay, everyone write
your name on This very
official document

08:27.074 --> 08:30.377
and consider
the first official

08:30.444 --> 08:32.045
Paradise dance academy
peace accord enacted.

08:32.112 --> 08:35.282
Hear ye, hurrah,
strawberry fields forever.

08:36.984 --> 08:39.653
You see what I did there?
I kofi annan-Ed their Butts.

08:39.720 --> 08:42.189
Very impressive.
Who's the Spinner?

08:42.256 --> 08:45.526
<i>Oh wow.</i>
<i>Where did she come from?</i>

08:45.592 --> 08:49.263
Oh, I have no idea
who that might be.
Huh, that's weird.

08:57.204 --> 08:59.039
- Madame Fanny?
- Sasha!

08:59.106 --> 09:02.276
Goodness, I didn't
hear you come in.

09:02.342 --> 09:04.044
- How are you?
- I'm fine. Who is that?

09:04.111 --> 09:06.647
- Who?
- her.

09:06.713 --> 09:09.016
The person dancing nonstop
in the middle of the floor.

09:09.082 --> 09:11.218
Oh her.

09:11.285 --> 09:13.353
- Well, that's--
- Did you call in the Ringer?

09:13.420 --> 09:15.022
I did! I'm sorry,
I didn't know
what else to do.

09:15.088 --> 09:19.259
- Is she going to be Clara?
- No, you are Clara.

09:19.326 --> 09:22.529
Well, is somebody going
to tell music-Box ballerina
over there?

09:22.596 --> 09:24.097
Yes, of course.

09:24.164 --> 09:27.367
I mean, it's too late
to send her back now.
Arrangements have been made.

09:27.434 --> 09:29.169
She'll be here
at least a week.

09:29.236 --> 09:31.038
I'll just give her
a different role.

09:31.104 --> 09:32.039
I wonder how
she'll feel about that.

09:32.105 --> 09:35.008
I don't know.
Do machines feel?

09:35.075 --> 09:37.311
- You tell her!
- What?

09:37.377 --> 09:40.147
Yes! As part
of your punishment,
you have to go over there

09:40.214 --> 09:42.883
- And tell her
she's not playing Clara.
- Are you afraid of her?

09:42.950 --> 09:45.853
No, I'm not
afraid of her.

09:45.919 --> 09:49.723
This is a life lesson.
Your behavior got us
into this situation,

09:49.790 --> 09:51.091
so your behavior should
get us out of it.

09:53.594 --> 09:56.330
- fine.
- Wait!

10:00.868 --> 10:03.504
Go!

10:06.974 --> 10:09.710
Hey.
I'm Sasha.

10:09.776 --> 10:12.546
Wow, your shoes
should be red.

10:12.613 --> 10:15.015
I wrap my feet
in cellophane so the blood
doesn't soak through.

10:15.082 --> 10:17.050
No, I didn't mean like--
Never mind.

10:17.117 --> 10:21.054
So there's been
a little mistake.

10:21.121 --> 10:22.990
You were
called down here to--

10:23.056 --> 10:25.392
To play Clara?
I know. I'm ready.

10:25.459 --> 10:28.428
Yeah well, you were
supposed to replace me,

10:28.495 --> 10:30.097
but now I'm back,
so you don't need to.

10:33.267 --> 10:35.636
- anymore.
- Replace you?

10:35.702 --> 10:37.037
- Yeah.
- Where were you?

10:37.104 --> 10:40.908
I, uh, quit ballet
for a while.

10:40.974 --> 10:43.110
- to do what?
- To...

10:43.177 --> 10:45.012
be a cheerleader.

10:45.078 --> 10:47.414
Oh!

10:48.949 --> 10:51.351
Yeah, so thanks
for coming,

10:51.418 --> 10:54.421
- But Bye!
- You know, I've seen
your kind before.

10:54.488 --> 10:57.691
You get into ballet
for the tutus.

10:57.758 --> 11:00.227
I did not get into ballet
for the tutus.

11:00.294 --> 11:02.029
But then you get older
and suddenly there's boys

11:02.095 --> 11:05.966
and clothes and...
cheerleading.

11:06.033 --> 11:08.035
Yeah Well, whatever,
I'm here now,

11:08.101 --> 11:12.272
- So I'm not going anywhere.
- We'll see.

11:12.339 --> 11:15.042
Look, madame Fanny
said she'd give you another
part to play if you--

11:15.108 --> 11:18.946
Could you stop dancing
for one freaking moment?!

11:19.012 --> 11:21.248
I'll stop dancing.
I'll stop dancing

11:21.315 --> 11:23.050
after I take my bow
in "the nutcracker"...

11:23.116 --> 11:25.752
as Clara.

11:36.997 --> 11:38.498
Hey, Rico,
your place looks great.

11:38.565 --> 11:40.901
Yeah, there's a lot
of freaking people in here.

11:40.968 --> 11:43.403
- I know. Great turnout.
- I mean they're everywhere.

11:43.470 --> 11:46.106
- They're using the bathrooms.
- That was part of the
ticket price--

11:46.173 --> 11:48.942
- Food, drinks, working toilets.
- But how long are they
going to stay?

11:49.009 --> 11:51.945
- the party's till 10:00.
- 10:00? That's like
four hours from now.

11:52.012 --> 11:53.547
- Who agreed to this?
- You did!

11:53.614 --> 11:55.849
Oh, what the frak!

11:55.916 --> 11:58.852
- Are you paying me a lot?
- You donated the place.

11:58.919 --> 12:01.388
- Yeah, that sounds like me.
- Have a drink.

12:01.455 --> 12:04.958
It will all
look better after a drink.
China, set him up good.

12:05.025 --> 12:07.861
- <i>You got it.</i>
- Ginny: Thanks so much
for coming.

12:07.928 --> 12:09.830
Melanie:
See you at the show!

12:09.897 --> 12:12.366
Okay, whose gross hand
do we have to shake next?

12:12.432 --> 12:13.800
I say we wait
a few minutes

12:13.867 --> 12:16.970
and let the four
different kinds of bird flu
sink into our pores

12:17.037 --> 12:19.306
before we go for
the malaria-Ebola trifecta.

12:19.373 --> 12:22.209
- I want to live in a bubble.
- Hey, don't look too closely,

12:22.276 --> 12:25.279
- But old man Purdee left
his fly unzipped again.
- ugh, I know.

12:25.345 --> 12:28.715
- I was looking for Carl.
- I think I saw him
under the sink.

12:30.984 --> 12:33.220
- Melanie, wrapper!
- That wasn't a short joke.

12:33.287 --> 12:34.855
He was literally
under the sink.

12:34.922 --> 12:36.590
He must've dropped
something.

12:36.657 --> 12:38.859
I didn't say he was
living under the sink, god.

12:38.926 --> 12:42.729
Stop following me.
I'm not Justin Bieber!

12:42.796 --> 12:43.864
Who?

12:43.931 --> 12:46.867
- Seriously?
- What if something happens?

12:46.934 --> 12:48.902
What if you get
abducted by aliens?

12:48.969 --> 12:52.272
What if some guy grabs you
on the sidewalk and throws
you in the back of a Van?

12:52.339 --> 12:54.708
- then I'd hope
you'd call the police.
- of course.

12:54.775 --> 12:56.577
After rehearsal.

12:57.578 --> 13:00.013
- Hey, Carl!
- Hey.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.349
- So many people here tonight.
- Love those boots.

13:02.416 --> 13:04.117
- Digging the hat.
- Okay?

13:04.184 --> 13:06.253
- You have any plans
for the summer?
- Camp.

13:06.320 --> 13:08.422
- S'mores!
- Awesome.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.891
Yeah, I'm going
to go now.

13:10.958 --> 13:13.026
Okay.
Bye, Carl.

13:13.093 --> 13:15.429
You're way taller
than Prince.

13:15.495 --> 13:18.365
- That was hard.
- I think I actually
pulled something.

13:20.367 --> 13:22.970
What?
Did the pizza bites
finally come out?

13:23.904 --> 13:25.606
<i>What are they</i>
<i>doing here, Ginny?</i>

13:25.672 --> 13:27.808
I mentioned
the fundraiser to Charlie
in one of our texts.

13:27.875 --> 13:29.676
I didn't know
you two were texting.

13:29.743 --> 13:31.812
We agreed
I wasn't going to talk
about Charlie to you.

13:31.879 --> 13:33.547
Gum wrapper, remember?

13:33.614 --> 13:37.117
Hey, Ginny, you look cute.
Who's the dude you're with?

13:37.184 --> 13:39.920
Very funny.
It's nice you bring
your wife everywhere.

13:39.987 --> 13:42.923
You wanna maybe go
somewhere where the scenery
is less revolting?

13:42.990 --> 13:44.958
- Um, sure.
- Cool.

13:45.025 --> 13:46.593
Later.

13:46.660 --> 13:49.363
I have to hand it to her,
Michelle really came through.

13:49.429 --> 13:53.133
- Look at all these people.
- You mean look at all of these
walking dollar signs.

13:53.200 --> 13:55.969
- Oh, Michael... but yes.
- ( laughs )

13:56.036 --> 13:59.239
So I don't want to say
I totally delivered, but...

14:00.974 --> 14:03.443
- But what?
- You're supposed to say
"you totally did."

14:03.510 --> 14:06.313
I am? I'm supposed
to say "Totally"?

14:06.380 --> 14:08.882
- I don't think so.
- Why won't she give me
my props?

14:08.949 --> 14:12.319
Just five minutes ago
she was saying that
you really came through.

14:12.386 --> 14:14.188
- You're kidding.
- don't tell her that.

14:14.254 --> 14:17.824
- Wait, what else did she say?
- She said that you were going
to be over here

14:17.891 --> 14:21.895
fishing for compliments,
but I said that you were
too good for that.

14:24.164 --> 14:26.033
- Never mind.
- <i>( both laughing )</i>

14:28.869 --> 14:31.138
Be right back.

14:31.205 --> 14:33.907
Don't do it.
The answer's never
in a citrus slice.

14:33.974 --> 14:36.043
Have a shot instead.

14:36.109 --> 14:38.378
I'm an idiot.

14:38.445 --> 14:41.348
Put that comment
into context before
I form a response.

14:41.415 --> 14:43.984
I totally blew it
with Carl.

14:44.051 --> 14:46.653
I didn't even realize
I liked him until
he was gone.

14:46.720 --> 14:48.589
Well, he didn't go far.
He's over there.

14:48.655 --> 14:51.525
Might as well be
in singapore, he's never
coming near me again.

14:51.592 --> 14:53.961
- You hurt his feelings, boo.
- I know.

14:54.027 --> 14:57.798
You did the damage,
now you have to
make it right.

14:57.865 --> 15:00.968
So get up and go
make it right.

15:10.410 --> 15:13.013
- What did you do?
- Just spreading
the yoda around.

15:13.080 --> 15:14.848
Oh my god.

15:14.915 --> 15:17.518
- is this on?
- Try the Veal!

15:17.584 --> 15:20.487
- What?
- Never mind.
Go on. Yay, boo.

15:20.554 --> 15:22.656
( crowd cheering )

15:22.723 --> 15:24.358
Thank you.

15:24.424 --> 15:27.394
Um, I'd like to take this
opportunity

15:27.461 --> 15:29.396
to say something

15:29.463 --> 15:31.064
here

15:31.131 --> 15:33.734
