31:54.817 --> 31:56.953
All right, okay...

31:59.022 --> 32:00.757
- ( groans ) crap.
- I have to go back on!

32:00.823 --> 32:02.659
Chill, Clara.
I have more in here.

32:02.725 --> 32:05.328
- Okay, got it.
- ( shrieking )

32:05.395 --> 32:07.463
what?
What--

32:07.530 --> 32:10.166
- ( shrieks )
- Melanie: <i>What the hell is it?</i>

32:10.233 --> 32:12.602
- Oh my god!
- Ginny: <i>My eyes are melting!</i>

32:12.669 --> 32:15.405
- This isn't
hairspray, it's Mace.
- You maced us?!

32:15.471 --> 32:18.274
- I maced you.
- Why, why would you do that?

32:18.341 --> 32:20.977
- It was an accident.
- Ahh, that's my music!

32:21.044 --> 32:23.112
- Where's the stage?
- There there.

33:04.887 --> 33:06.389
- boo!
- <i>Here!</i>

33:06.456 --> 33:10.059
- Need a specific--
Up, down, right, left.
- <i>here.</i>

33:10.126 --> 33:12.195
- here.
- ahhh!

33:12.261 --> 33:15.398
I found you.
Uhhh ahhh ahhh.

33:15.465 --> 33:17.200
- ( moaning )
- Water, I've got water.

33:17.266 --> 33:20.069
Everyone, try to get your face
in front of the flying water!

33:20.136 --> 33:21.638
- Sasha: <i>Help me!</i>
- Sasha.

33:21.704 --> 33:23.272
- <i>Michelle?</i>
- Sasha!

33:23.339 --> 33:24.240
- Marco?
- <i>Polo!</i>

33:24.307 --> 33:26.109
- Marco?
- Polo!

33:28.411 --> 33:30.546
Ohhh, crap.
Okay, lemme try and find--

33:30.613 --> 33:32.849
something.

33:36.419 --> 33:38.921
I told you I'd be Clara.

33:42.291 --> 33:44.661
<i>( dancers clamoring )</i>

33:52.669 --> 33:55.004
( audience clamoring )

33:55.071 --> 33:57.707
<i>( sirens approaching )</i>

34:13.556 --> 34:15.558
( chattering )

34:16.926 --> 34:19.462
- How are your eyes?
- The left one's back.

34:19.529 --> 34:21.898
- Michelle:
<i>Ray ray, Stephanie.</i>
- that's good.

34:21.964 --> 34:24.200
- Girl: <i>Over here.</i>
- <i>Matisse?</i>

34:24.267 --> 34:26.769
- I hate Charlie.
- <i>right here.</i>

34:26.836 --> 34:30.206
- Michelle: <i>Katrina?</i>
<i>Katrina?</i>
- Me too.

34:30.273 --> 34:32.175
<i>- I'm here.</i>
<i>- Stephanie, Stephanie?</i>

34:32.241 --> 34:34.911
- <i>Yeah?</i>
- Anna Maria,
Anna Maria, Anna Maria?

34:34.978 --> 34:37.113
- We don't have
an Anna Maria.
- We don't?

34:37.180 --> 34:39.449
- No.
- Who's the girl
I call Anna Maria?

34:39.515 --> 34:41.851
- Casey.
- Oh. Casey!

34:41.918 --> 34:44.354
- <i>Here.</i>
- Hey, kid,
you can't go four months

34:44.420 --> 34:47.023
letting someone
call you Anna Maria.
A little life tip for you.

34:47.090 --> 34:48.691
- You're Michelle?
- Yes, how are the kids?

34:48.758 --> 34:50.893
We flushed their eyes,
gave them ice,
everyone will be fine.

34:50.960 --> 34:52.829
- I just need to check you out.
- Not now, I'm busy.

34:52.895 --> 34:54.330
- Angel!
- <i>Yeah?</i>

34:54.397 --> 34:56.232
- I need to check
you out now, please.
- Look, lady,

34:56.299 --> 34:58.835
I'm not gonna
leave this hallway, okay?
I'm the one who maced these kids

34:58.901 --> 35:01.237
and I am going to be here
until every last one
of them is--

35:01.304 --> 35:03.272
I'm talking to a piece
of cardboard, right?

35:03.339 --> 35:05.475
- Yep.
- after you.

35:10.913 --> 35:13.950
Hey.
I know you.

35:14.017 --> 35:16.185
- Yeah?
- You're on
the basketball team.

35:16.252 --> 35:18.821
<i>Was </i>on
the basketball team.

35:18.888 --> 35:19.989
What happened?

35:20.056 --> 35:22.959
You dribble right,
you dribble left,
you dribble right,

35:23.026 --> 35:26.496
you dribble left-- That's
a lot of dribbling without
having some sort of stroke.

35:26.562 --> 35:29.265
- I hear you.
- I'm Roman.

35:29.332 --> 35:32.068
- I thought your name was Tyler.
- Roman's my middle name.

35:32.135 --> 35:35.738
- It works better with the hair.
- that's the thought process.

35:35.805 --> 35:40.043
- So what are you in for?
- Mosh pit got a little
too intense.

35:40.109 --> 35:43.179
- What about you?
- My ballet Teacher maced us

35:43.246 --> 35:46.082
- During a production
of "the nutcracker."
- Wow!

35:46.149 --> 35:49.652
- Maybe I should
be taking ballet.
- It's rougher than you think.

35:49.719 --> 35:53.523
- Apparently.
- So this look-- New?

35:53.589 --> 35:55.858
- Fairly recent.
- No more varsity Joe?

35:55.925 --> 35:58.828
I think we have
officially parted ways.

35:58.895 --> 36:01.864
- You're Sasha, right?
- Yeah.

36:01.931 --> 36:04.100
My middle name's
Henrietta, so...

36:04.167 --> 36:06.202
Sasha it is.

36:09.172 --> 36:10.907
- there you are.
- Family?

36:10.974 --> 36:12.475
- Sort of.
- I guess.

36:12.542 --> 36:14.944
- Daughter-in-Law
for a minute or so.
- mother-In-Law for a minute.

36:15.011 --> 36:16.479
- Landlord now.
- don't know what that
makes me now.

36:16.546 --> 36:18.748
Whatever. Come on in.
I'll be right back.
You'll be okay?

36:18.815 --> 36:20.650
- No.
- attagirl!

36:26.689 --> 36:29.325
- So how are you?
- Face hurts.

36:29.392 --> 36:30.960
Yes. Large doses

36:31.027 --> 36:33.830
of self-Inflicted Pepper spray
will do that to a person.

36:33.896 --> 36:35.765
Yeah.
I'm so sorry.

36:35.832 --> 36:39.002
You maced
my entire production
of "the nutcracker."

36:39.068 --> 36:40.737
I don't think
I got everyone.

36:40.803 --> 36:43.740
No, you did.
It was a clean sweep.
Nailed every last dewdrop.

36:43.806 --> 36:46.776
- I'm really sorry.
- You know I had to cancel
the shows.

36:46.843 --> 36:48.945
Two whole weeks, canceled.

36:49.012 --> 36:50.947
- I'm--
- You're sorry?
Yes, I heard.

36:51.014 --> 36:54.584
Do you know how bad this is?
I will be lucky if these parents

36:54.651 --> 36:56.886
don't drag me into court
and have me flogged.

36:56.953 --> 36:59.155
They don't flog people
in california.

36:59.222 --> 37:02.058
- You're a lawyer?
You know the law?
- I know they don't flog.

37:02.125 --> 37:05.194
Well, I don't know that.
I'm not as wise and worldly
as you are.

37:05.261 --> 37:08.331
I didn't live
in vegas and date gangsters.
I just tried to teach ballet

37:08.398 --> 37:12.201
to a bunch of kids-- The same
kids who are sitting out in
the hallway of this hospital.

37:17.840 --> 37:20.476
I should've known something
like this would happen.

37:20.543 --> 37:23.479
- Why? 'cause I was involved?
- Bad luck was in the air.

37:23.546 --> 37:26.582
When I got up this morning
and Michael was gone
just like that,

37:26.649 --> 37:28.651
- It was a sign.
- Michael's gone?

37:28.718 --> 37:30.486
- Yes.
- Why would he go?

37:30.553 --> 37:33.189
I explained
everything to him.

37:33.256 --> 37:35.792
What are you talking about?

37:35.858 --> 37:37.627
I told him about the cabin,

37:37.694 --> 37:39.962
about what you thought
Montana was going to be--

37:40.029 --> 37:42.231
you and him being
together finally.

37:42.298 --> 37:45.068
- Why would you do that?
- I was trying to help.

37:45.134 --> 37:48.137
- help who, me?
- Fanny, you don't
explain to a man

37:48.204 --> 37:52.408
you want to be with him
permanently, of course he goes
and buys a place for himself.

37:52.475 --> 37:56.045
And you know all this
based on what? Your perfect
relationship record?

37:56.112 --> 37:58.581
- I--
- 30 years I've been
with this man.

37:58.648 --> 38:01.851
For 30 years
he's felt free,
unencumbered.

38:01.918 --> 38:05.288
He's been able to live
the exact life he wanted
and we were happy.

38:05.355 --> 38:08.725
- You never saw each other.
- even when I asked him to hang
around a little longer

38:08.791 --> 38:11.728
he knew I wasn't trying
to change him or tie him down.

38:11.794 --> 38:14.731
And then you, with your
extraordinarily big mouth,

38:14.797 --> 38:17.867
you drive him away in one day.
What is wrong with you?

38:17.934 --> 38:20.236
<i>You don't know me</i>
<i>well enough by now</i>

38:20.303 --> 38:22.872
to know that if I wanted him
to know about the cabin

38:22.939 --> 38:26.643
and my plans and what
I expected to happen,
I would've told him myself?

38:26.709 --> 38:29.779
You are the bad luck!
Ever since you got here,

38:29.846 --> 38:32.015
ever since Hubbell--

38:39.055 --> 38:41.290
I have to go outside
and deal with the parents.

38:41.357 --> 38:44.627
You should probably stay
in here a little while longer.

38:51.634 --> 38:53.636
<i>( street noise, door closes )</i>

39:00.310 --> 39:01.811
Hi, I'm Michelle Simms.

39:09.419 --> 39:10.520
<i>( music playing )</i>

39:10.586 --> 39:12.555
♪ Maybe this time ♪

39:12.622 --> 39:15.491
♪ I'll be lucky ♪

39:15.558 --> 39:20.763
♪ maybe this time
he'll stay ♪

39:22.465 --> 39:24.634
♪ maybe this time ♪

39:24.701 --> 39:27.737
♪ for the first time ♪

39:27.804 --> 39:33.643
♪ love won't hurry away ♪

39:33.710 --> 39:38.381
♪ he will hold me fast ♪

39:39.816 --> 39:43.753
♪ I'll be home at last ♪

39:46.022 --> 39:50.393
♪ not a loser anymore ♪

39:50.460 --> 39:53.730
♪ like the last time and ♪

39:53.796 --> 39:56.899
♪ the time before ♪

39:58.167 --> 40:00.570
♪ Everybody ♪

40:00.636 --> 40:03.706
♪ loves a Winner ♪

40:03.773 --> 40:08.611
♪ so nobody loves me ♪

40:09.612 --> 40:12.448
♪ lady peaceful ♪

40:12.515 --> 40:15.652
♪ lady happy ♪

40:15.718 --> 40:19.922
♪ that's what
I long to be ♪

40:21.724 --> 40:27.296
♪ all the odds are
in my favor ♪

40:27.363 --> 40:32.101
♪ something's
bound to begin ♪

40:33.503 --> 40:36.439
♪ it's gotta happen ♪

40:36.506 --> 40:39.542
♪ happen sometime ♪

40:39.609 --> 40:44.580
♪ maybe this time
I'll win... ♪

40:54.390 --> 40:56.526
Hello?

40:56.592 --> 40:58.294
What did you think?

41:00.363 --> 41:02.699
Wow.

41:02.765 --> 41:04.867
Hey.

41:04.934 --> 41:06.703
Where have you been?

41:06.769 --> 41:08.571
<i>Oh, I've been around.</i>

41:08.638 --> 41:11.641
- <i>( traffic noise stops )</i>
- Everything looks
so different now.

41:11.708 --> 41:15.912
No, nothing's different.
Everything's exactly where
it was when you left.

41:15.979 --> 41:19.182
I've tried really hard
not to rock the boat.

41:19.248 --> 41:22.085
You're here
to rock the boat.

41:23.252 --> 41:25.688
You know, she always
wanted me to dance.

41:25.755 --> 41:28.858
( laughs )
Oh, what I would've given
for a picture of that.

41:28.925 --> 41:31.394
Yeah.
She would've liked a girl.

41:34.664 --> 41:36.733
Hubbell?

41:38.067 --> 41:41.704
- They're broken.
- I just wanted to see
the frogs.

41:41.771 --> 41:44.073
I'm doing it again.
I'm ruining everything.

41:44.140 --> 41:47.043
- You can fix it.
- I don't even know
that I'm doing it.

41:47.110 --> 41:50.246
I need glue.
You're my glue.

41:50.313 --> 41:53.449
- These four are fine.
- I was supposed to
take care of them.

41:53.516 --> 41:55.585
I was supposed
to help them.

41:55.652 --> 41:57.654
I was supposed to
be better for them.

41:57.720 --> 42:00.957
I don't want them
to be like me.

42:01.024 --> 42:03.226
You should look around.

42:03.292 --> 42:05.395
Everything is different.

42:06.896 --> 42:10.099
- I miss you.
- It's funny when
things happen.

42:10.166 --> 42:12.702
Hubbell,
tell me something.

42:12.769 --> 42:14.003
What?

42:14.070 --> 42:15.805
Would it have worked?

42:15.872 --> 42:18.541
Would I have stayed?

42:18.608 --> 42:21.344
P.A.:
<i>dr. Freedman, Dial 3996.</i>

42:21.411 --> 42:24.547
<i>Social services,</i>
<i>call the fourth floor</i>
<i>nurses' station.</i>

42:26.683 --> 42:29.285
- Man: <i>Gone, Fanny, she's gone!</i>
- Fanny: <i>I know you're</i>
<i>all upset.</i>

42:29.352 --> 42:32.121
Man: <i>I'm not upset.</i>
<i>I love picking my kid up</i>
<i>from the emergency room.</i>

42:32.188 --> 42:34.724
Woman:
<i>That woman is never around</i>
<i>our children ever again.</i>

42:34.791 --> 42:36.893
Man:
She's unstable. The other
night in the oyster bar,

42:36.959 --> 42:38.861
she had sex
with that bartender
at the party.

42:38.928 --> 42:40.363
Man #2:
Who cares what
she did at the bar?

42:40.430 --> 42:41.664
Man:
I care what she did
at the bar.

42:41.731 --> 42:43.499
I eat brunch there
on sundays.

42:43.566 --> 42:46.502
- Fanny: Everyone
needs to calm down.
- Woman: She maced our kids!

42:46.569 --> 42:49.138
- Sprayed Pepper spray
in their faces.
- Doctor: Hey, you need to move.

42:49.205 --> 42:51.674
- We have to work here.
- Fanny: Please, let's just
talk outside.

42:51.741 --> 42:53.643
- Man: She's gone, Fanny!
- Woman: Exactly.

42:55.878 --> 42:57.714
"O captain,
my captain!"

43:01.884 --> 43:03.953
"O captain,
my captain!"

43:06.856 --> 43:08.524
BOTH:
"o captain, my captain!"

43:10.860 --> 43:12.395
I don't know
what that means.

43:12.462 --> 43:14.664
- Just get up.
- I don't watch Cable.

43:15.898 --> 43:17.900
You know that at the end
of the movie

43:17.967 --> 43:19.635
the guy had to leave
anyhow, right?

43:22.939 --> 43:24.741
Thank you, boys.

43:26.542 --> 43:28.645
Thank you, girls.

43:28.711 --> 43:29.712
Thank you.
